Third-Party Components
----------------------

This repository may reference or include third-party components that
are licensed under their own terms. Such components retain their
original licenses and are NOT covered by this license. Notable
third-party components include, without limitation:

  - Nordic Semiconductor nRF5 SDK and CMSIS device files
    (Nordic 5-Clause License). Vendor files are not redistributed in this
    publication — see `Main/Project/src/nRF/README.md` for restore steps.

  - SEGGER startup and runtime files such as `thumb_crt0.s`
    (SEGGER BSD-style license; header preserved in-file).

  - The GSM audio decoder used in the original product has been omitted
    from this publication due to license incompatibility. See
    `Main/Project/src/Audio/GSM_REMOVED.md`.

  - LZSS encoder/decoder by Haruhiko Okumura (public domain). Both the
    embedded decoder at `Main/Project/src/Compression/lzssdec.c` and the
    host encoder/decoder at `Tools/LZSS/` derive from this reference
    implementation; the public-domain notice is preserved in-file.

  - Portions of code in `Main/Project/src/fpmath.h` (the fix16 / fix32
    primitives), `Main/Project/src/utils.c` (the approximated
    2D-distance routines), and `Main/Project/src/Pod/Misc/fxpt_atan2.h`
    (the fix16 helper macros that wrap the atan2 implementation) are
    adapted from SGDK (Sega Genesis Development Kit) by Stéphane
    Dallongeville (https://github.com/Stephane-D/SGDK), licensed under
    the MIT License. The full MIT notice is reproduced at the top of
    `fpmath.h`; SGDK-derived sections in `utils.c` and
    `fxpt_atan2.h` are annotated in-file. These portions are
    redistributed under those same MIT terms.

  - `Main/Project/src/Pod/Misc/fix_fft.c` (and its `.h`), together with
    an inline 8-bit variant included in `Main/Project/src/Pod/TestMode.c`,
    are the canonical **public-domain** fixed-point FFT routines:
        Written by:    Tom Roberts                  11/8/89
        Made portable: Malcolm Slaney               12/15/94
        Enhanced:      Dimitrios P. Bouras          14 Jun 2006
    The original attribution block is preserved in-file.

  - `Main/Project/src/Pod/Misc/fxpt_atan2.c` (and its `.h`) is a
    fixed-point atan2 implementation:
        Copyright (C) 2012, Xo Wang — MIT License.
    The original MIT notice is preserved in-file.

  - The synth runtime in `Main/Project/src/Audio/synth.c` and its
    header `synth.h`, together with the host-side `Tools/ModConverter/`
    tooling, are derived from DuinoTune by Blake Livingston
    (https://github.com/blakelivingston/DuinoTune), licensed under the
    MIT License. The synth files were heavily modified for the Melbits
    POD firmware (real-time scheduling, LED + vibration channels, GSM
    PCM voice integration). The original MIT notice is reproduced in
    each file; modifications are released under those same MIT terms.

  - `Main/Project/src/Pod/Misc/crc16.c` and its header `crc16.h` are
    redistributed from the Nordic nRF5 SDK under Nordic Semiconductor's
    5-Clause License. The full Nordic license header is preserved
    in-file.

Refer to the headers of individual files for their applicable terms.

